UnDenied

The Problem:
Every year hundreds of millions of official letters are sent to ordinary people — insurance denials, eviction notices, benefits rejections, school suspensions, medical bills, credit disputes. These letters are written by lawyers on purpose to confuse people into giving up. 80% of people never appeal. Of those who do, 80% win. That means most denials are wrongful and people just don't fight back — not because they're wrong but because they couldn't understand a letter.
Low income families. Elderly people. Immigrants. Single mothers. These are the people getting crushed by letters designed to intimidate them into silence.